---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon";
import ContentSection from "~/components/content-section.astro";
---

<ContentSection title="Just ship less" id="intro">
  <Icon slot="eyebrow" name="logomark" class="h-32" />
  <Fragment slot="lead">The World's First Multi-Graph Key-Value Merkle-Tree Persistence Layer, EinsteinDB incorporates updates to the Causet Formalism; borrowing from Datomic and JanusGraph. This formalism enables powerful query optimization and data modeling capabilities in EinsteinDB.
      <span class="text-primary">RinconX: EisensteinDB introduces a library called RinconX, which composes Xpander Graphs for the sparse computation of tabular data. </span> It leverages principles from the Vector Anisotropic Quantization Scheme practiced in MIPS (Maximal Inner Products) factorization scheme.
    <span class="text-primary"></span>
      Predictive Analytics and Chaos Engineering via Smooth Parametrized ML-based Predictive Quandaries<span class="text-primary">for continued, merge-append, amd d appended IPFS</span> This protocol offers advanced predictive analytics capabilities using machine learning techniques, with a focus on chaos engineering practices seen at companies like Uber, Netflix, Carnegie Mellon, and Oracle.
  </Fragment>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <a
      href="https://www.github.com/YosiSF/EinsteinDB"
      class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 border-2 border-current px-6 py-4"
    >
      <Icon pack="mdi" name="telescope" class="h-8" />
      <span> Open Source and Serverless Envoy Proxy Available with LLVM BERT Encoder/Decoder</span>
    </a>
    <a
      href="https://www.github.com/YosiSF/MilevaDB"
      class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3 border-2 border-current px-6 py-4"
    >
      <Icon pack="mdi" name="rocket" class="h-8" />
      <span>Integrating open-source technologies such as Envoy Proxy with serverless computing frameworks, leveraging an LLVM-based encoder/decoder using Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT).</span>
    </a>

  </div>
</ContentSection>
